{"id": "EUVD-2025-16380", "enisaUuid": "da72a4f4-7001-3d1b-9699-3691fb092942", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nKVM: arm64: Fix uninitialized memcache pointer in user_mem_abort()\n\nCommit fce886a60207 (\"KVM: arm64: Plumb the pKVM MMU in KVM\") made the\ninitialization of the local memcache variable in user_mem_abort()\nconditional, leaving a codepath where it is used uninitialized via\nkvm_pgtable_stage2_map().\n\nThis can fail on any path that requires a stage-2 allocation\nwithout transition via a permission fault or dirty logging.\n\nFix this by making sure that memcache is always valid.", "datePublished": "2025-05-29T15:31:09", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-14T18:31:21", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-37996", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/157dbc4a321f5bb6f8b6c724d12ba720a90f1a7c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a26d50f8a4a5049e956984797b5d0dedea4bbb18"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-37996", "GHSA-v8pp-m355-r6cw"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "5e5a0656-daca-3a58-b1bb-8557419e1e5d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "fce886a6020734d6253c2c5a3bc285e385cc5496 <a26d50f8a4a5049e956984797b5d0dedea4bbb18"}, {"id": "a6369e82-7970-3663-86bd-1fb4aba55b3a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "aa1eac17-5ea6-3fc3-a0cc-e79e553132cc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "fce886a6020734d6253c2c5a3bc285e385cc5496 <157dbc4a321f5bb6f8b6c724d12ba720a90f1a7c"}, {"id": "c7ca41ba-cacd-3e11-8b50-098d3d5ced77", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14.7"}, {"id": "cd09a3f1-9b2b-31c2-989a-22e7458c6778", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.14"}, {"id": "f3da5255-7472-3478-9614-6439c9a3e047", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "0c6401e3-b4e8-3f0f-92c3-c60c15147918", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": fal